reviewText: Some good segments some bad ones in this anthology. It's a mixed bag. A few are horribly low budget and a few aren't.  It's still a ton of fun and worth a peek. Some great gore and fun in this one.

reviewText: A complete work of art! Good indie horror compilations like this are hard to come by. So glad I found this one! It's everything you'd hope for in a campy good times horror flick, and I loved the host!

reviewText: I have loved short horror film comps like this from way back in the day. Really great too when I don't have time to watch a full movie. I'll just watch one while I eat lunch. ;)

reviewText: This is an awesome collection of tales from some of today's top upcoming indie filmmakers, the Adam greens & Tim Sullivans of the future are right here, with the comeback of the Great Horror anthology with films like Nightmare Alley & Chillerama, Scarlet Fry's Junkfood Horrorfest & Theatre of bizarre, this is one of the better ones i've seen in a long time, I cant wait to get my hands on the official DVD. Features Shawn C. Phillips. Also check out Treasure Chest of Horrors which is another awesome anthology that coming in june from the same producers. These are not films you want to miss especially if you love stuff like Trick or Treat, The Basement, Creepshow, Its got all the Gore, Horror & Humor you could ever want. A+
